                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1373b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="85" xml:id="d613fn85">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date to the Minister in Paraguay as telegram
                        No. 37.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-18T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 18, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Please present the following note to the Bolivian Government on next Monday
                    September 21st on behalf of the neutral representatives in Washington: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The representatives in Washington of the neutral Governments have
                            learned with great pleasure that both Bolivia and Paraguay have accepted
                            the suggestion of their Governments to authorize duly accredited
                            representatives to study and draw up a pact of non-aggression in the
                            Chaco in order to maintain peace and tranquillity there until
                            negotiations can be entered into which will carry the territorial
                            controversy to an equitable and final ending. In view of this the
                            neutral representatives suggest that the first meeting take place at
                            Washington on Thursday, October 1st, and accordingly have the honor to
                            suggest that the Bolivian Government instruct its representative in this
                            sense. A similar proposal is being made to the Paraguayan
                            Government.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
